This paper deals with the implementation of proof assistants and higher-order logic programming languages, which falls under the category of Programming Languages (cs.PL). It specifically focuses on the evaluation of lambda-terms, which is related to the Lambda Calculus (cs.LO) and the study of abstract machines. The paper also discusses the properties of the machine, such as correctness and completeness, which are related to Software Engineering (cs.SE). The study of decoding the machine into the Linear Substitution Calculus is related to Logic in Computer Science (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the overhead of the machine, which is related to Formal Languages and Automata Theory (cs.FL).
